1:23:13.684 --> 1:23:16.165
I think that I will feel very
proud if one day in Senegal

1:23:16.208 --> 1:23:18.036
they say it doesn't
exist anymore.

1:23:22.345 --> 1:23:25.043
Graffiti, it's a lifestyle.

1:23:25.087 --> 1:23:26.523
It's a culture.

1:23:26.566 --> 1:23:31.571
And if we insert the program
against domestic violence,

1:23:31.615 --> 1:23:37.055
the talk about gender
inside this culture,

1:23:37.099 --> 1:23:40.537
we are changing
the way that people think.

1:23:45.977 --> 1:23:47.718
I mean, I'm not trying
to save the world.

1:23:47.761 --> 1:23:49.676
So many people say they are.

1:23:49.720 --> 1:23:53.593
I think it's a great idea,
but it's not possible
to get to everyone.

1:23:53.637 --> 1:23:56.292
But I'm just happy
to get to as many as I can.

1:23:56.335 --> 1:23:58.685
And even if it's one
and I die, that's fine.

1:23:58.729 --> 1:24:01.645
I just want to get as many
as I can on their feet.

1:24:05.779 --> 1:24:09.696
I feel all women
are creative in this world.

1:24:09.740 --> 1:24:15.137
But sometimes,
because of our
society's structure--

1:24:15.180 --> 1:24:19.793
because of the
patriarchal structures,
because of the gender structure,

1:24:19.837 --> 1:24:23.406
they stop themselves
to take action.

1:24:25.451 --> 1:24:29.194
But if that comes when women
come with that action,

1:24:29.238 --> 1:24:34.895
I think that will bring great
changes in the society.

1:24:34.939 --> 1:24:38.334
So I always
encourage young people,
young women, do.

1:24:38.377 --> 1:24:41.728
Do something!
If you have idea,
be bold with that.

1:24:43.817 --> 1:24:49.345
But I have trust, belief,
with all women.

1:24:49.388 --> 1:24:51.347
Women are creative.
